nodeList.name: Touch Drag and Drop
nodeList.description: Drag and Drop refers to the action of selecting an object, moving it around, and then dropping it by letting go. To use this subgraph click the object selector box to change which Scene Object is being dragged. Snap to Center will make the object's pivot snap to the exact position of your touch when you first begin the drag. Global Grab Empty is a slot to input a global variable that tracks if your touch is already grabbing other objects. Leave it checked if not using global variables.
